	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Moscow - Russia's defence ministry said on Friday that Moscow was extending a "humanitarian pause" in Aleppo until 16:00 GMT on Saturday to allow civilians and armed rebels to leave the city. "At the request of representatives of the UN and other international organisations, a decision by the Russian president extends the humanitarian pause in the Aleppo region by another 24 hours," senior military official Sergei Rudskoi told reporters. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  